WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.692 --> 00:00:06.116
Born on 13 October, 1911.

00:00:06.770 --> 00:00:09.526
His parents christened him Kumudlal Ganguly.

00:00:09.929 --> 00:00:13.217
The film industry knew him as Ashok Kumar.

00:00:13.479 --> 00:00:16.829
And his friends called
him Dada Moni, lovingly.

00:00:21.624 --> 00:00:24.782
Ashok Kumar began with Bombay Talkies.

00:00:25.094 --> 00:00:28.152
He used to work as a laboratory assistant.

00:00:28.444 --> 00:00:29.983
There is an anecdote..

00:00:30.175 --> 00:00:31.613
..that one of Devika Rani's leading men..

00:00:31.693 --> 00:00:34.601
..Najbul Hussain was absconding.

00:00:34.844 --> 00:00:37.217
Because of which, the
co-owner of Bombay Talkies..

00:00:37.429 --> 00:00:39.380
..Himanshu Rai decided to give Ashok Kumar..

00:00:39.561 --> 00:00:40.769
..the leading man's role.

00:00:51.620 --> 00:00:54.094
Devika Rani and Ashok Kumar made a fine pair.

00:00:54.325 --> 00:00:55.482
In the film "Achhut Kanya"..

00:00:55.653 --> 00:00:57.635
..they were appreciated.

00:00:57.857 --> 00:00:59.678
After that, they worked in the films "Izzat"..

00:00:59.869 --> 00:01:02.827
.."Savitri" and "Nirmala".

00:01:03.098 --> 00:01:06.981
His star shone bright with the film Kismat.

00:01:07.163 --> 00:01:09.969
He played an anti-hero in the film.

00:01:10.261 --> 00:01:12.655
He always took risks.

00:01:12.817 --> 00:01:16.538
And with this film, he made a
unique mark in the industry.

00:01:32.174 --> 00:01:36.217
For Bombay Talkies, he produced many films.

00:01:36.377 --> 00:01:38.873
Of which Mahal stands apart.

00:01:39.064 --> 00:01:41.086
His pairing with the tragedy queen..

00:01:41.166 --> 00:01:43.671
..Meena Kumari was admired, too.

00:01:43.963 --> 00:01:46.719
They starred together in many films.

00:01:46.930 --> 00:01:48.912
Whether, it was "Parineeti", "Bahu Begum".

00:01:49.123 --> 00:01:50.703
"Pakeezah", "Ek Hi Raasta".

00:01:50.946 --> 00:01:52.433
"Bandish". Or, "Arti".

00:01:52.513 --> 00:01:55.803
Their performances in these
films were highly appreciated.

00:01:56.497 --> 00:01:58.881
You've wronged me? How did you wrong me..?

00:02:01.899 --> 00:02:02.322
It's you?

00:02:02.583 --> 00:02:04.394
He was one of the actors..

00:02:04.615 --> 00:02:08.477
..who worked on the big and small screen too.

00:02:08.810 --> 00:02:10.198
A TV series of the 80's, "Humlog"..

00:02:10.370 --> 00:02:13.488
..which featured him as an anchor..

00:02:13.699 --> 00:02:15.701
..is still fresh in people's minds.

00:02:25.947 --> 00:02:27.244
Gradually, he brought his..

00:02:27.429 --> 00:02:30.450
..younger brothers into the film industry.

00:02:30.721 --> 00:02:32.315
Anoop Kumar became an actor.

00:02:32.395 --> 00:02:35.174
And Kishore Kumar was a singer and actor.

00:02:41.368 --> 00:02:42.415
At one point in time..

00:02:42.571 --> 00:02:45.868
..he stopped celebrating his birthday.

00:02:46.133 --> 00:02:49.165
This was on 13th October, 1987.

00:02:49.450 --> 00:02:53.794
Kishore Kumar his brother hosted
a surprise party for him.

00:02:54.044 --> 00:02:57.169
To celebrate his birthday.

00:02:57.405 --> 00:03:00.295
The entire film industry came to his house.

00:03:00.765 --> 00:03:01.905
Dada Moni arrived too.

00:03:02.245 --> 00:03:06.875
But Kishore Kumar passed away on that day.

00:03:07.145 --> 00:03:10.575
Dada Moni or Ashok Kumar was
one of the few actors..

00:03:10.785 --> 00:03:13.475
..who have seen every aspect
of the film industry.

00:03:16.535 --> 00:03:17.345
It's you?

00:03:17.955 --> 00:03:18.905
It's Neelima.

00:03:19.115 --> 00:03:21.475
I wrote to you. - Yes, Neelima.

